A member of the COVID-19 government response team (L) asks questions to a resident during a door to door COVID-19 coronavirus screening in Westdene, Johannesburg. JOHANNESBURG - Six provinces reported COVID-19 related deaths in the last 24 hours. The countrywide death toll has now topped 8,500. The Health Department reported a 173 new coronavirus related deaths. READ: Threat of a COVID-19 generation Fourty-five patients died in Mpumalanga, 37 in Gauteng, 31 from the Western Cape, 28 from the North West, 20 in the Eastern Cape and 12 in KZN. Sixty-nine percent of people who tested positive, have already recovered. Only around 5,400 new cases have been confirmed in the latest health department report. Less than 22,000 tests were conducted since the last report - much lower than the almost 35,000 tests reported in the previous 24-hour cycle. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8 am to 4 pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.